==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rose-pink
<hw>Rose"-pink`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
a pink color like that of the rose, or like the pigment called <xex>rose
pink</xex>. See <cref>Rose pink</cref>, under <er>Rose</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disposed to clothe everything with roseate hues;
hence, sentimental.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Rose-pink</xex> piety.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roser</ent>⟦br⟧
